cription: Lanham : Lexington Books/Fortress Academic, [2022] | Includes &#8232;bibliographical references and index. | Summary: “In The Nonviolent &#8232;Apocalypse, Jeffrey D. Meyers argues that Revelation’s famously violent &#8232;visions are actually acts of nonviolent resistance to the Roman Empire. &#8232;Using insights from biblical studies and scholarship on nonviolence, &#8232;Meyers shows how Revelation both engages in and calls for acts of &#8232;nonviolent resistance”—Provided by publisher.</w:t></w:r></w:p></w:comment></w:comments>